<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 02 at 6:06PM EDT  by NWS Columbia</headline>
<description>...INCREASED FIRE DANGER ON SUNDAY DUE TO CRITICALLY DRY FUELS AND
LOW RELATIVE HUMIDITY...
At the request of the South Carolina Forestry Commission, this
increased fire danger statement is being issued for parts of the
northern Midlands, Pee Dee region, and eastern Midlands.
Dry, high pressure will build over the region on Sunday resulting
in critically low minimum relative humidities around 20 percent.
The Forestry Commission indicates that fuels are critically dry
and combined with very low relative humidity values and some gusty
northwesterly winds, there will be an increased fire danger
threat. Outdoor burning is discouraged.</description>
